Day 1 – Advanced Types

Topics:

Intersection types (&)
Literal types ("success" | "error")
Union types refresher
Type guards (typeof, instanceof)
keyof and typeof operators
Conditional types (T extends U ? X : Y)

Practice:

Create a union type for status = "success" | "error" | "loading"
Write a function that accepts a string | number and returns a string describing the type
Use keyof to get keys of an interface { name: string; age: number }
Day 2 – Classes & OOP

Topics:

Class syntax, constructors
public, private, protected
Readonly and static properties
Getters and setters
Inheritance
Abstract classes

Practice:

Create a Person class with name and age, add a greet() method
Extend Person into Employee with salary
Create an abstract class Shape with area() method, implement in Circle and Rectangle
Day 3 – Generics

Topics:

Generic functions
Generic interfaces and types
Constraints (T extends U)
Generic utility patterns

Practice:

Write a generic identity<T>(arg: T): T function
Create a generic Stack<T> class with push and pop
Constrain a generic function to accept only objects with a name property
Day 4 – Utility Types & Advanced Patterns

Topics:

Partial<T>, Required<T>
Pick<T, K> and Omit<T, K>
Record<K, T>
Nested objects & optional chaining

Practice:

Create a User interface, then use Partial<User> to update only some properties
Use Pick<User, "name"> to create a type with only name
Create a Record<string, number> for product stock counts

Day 5 – Modules & External JS Libraries

Topics:

export / import syntax
Default vs named exports
Using @types packages
Declaring modules for untyped JS

Practice:

Split a project into 2 files and import/export functions
Install @types/lodash and type a lodash function
Create a .d.ts file for a small untyped JS module
Day 6 – Advanced Function Types

Topics:

Function overloads
this in TS functions
Callback typing
Optional function properties in interfaces

Practice:

Write a function with 2 overloads: (x: number, y: number) and (x: string, y: string)
Define an interface with a method that optionally accepts a callback function
Use this type in a class method
Day 7 – Real-World TypeScript & Mini Project

Topics:

API data typing
TS with arrays of nested objects
Practical patterns for React/Node (optional)
TS config tuning (tsconfig.json)

Practice / Mini Project Idea:

Build a Todo App in TypeScript:
Todo interface with id, text, completed
Class or functions to add/remove/update todos
Generic functions for filtering by completed
Optional chaining for safe property access